  "type": "page",
  "link": "https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/success\/softbellys-inc-v-michael-bivens-et-al\/",
  "title": { "rendered": "Softbelly&#8217;s, Inc. v. Michael Bivens" },
  "content": {
    "rendered": "<div id=\"pl-469\" class=\"panel-layout\">\n<div id=\"pg-469-0\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\u00a0<\/div>\n<div id=\"pg-469-1\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\n<div id=\"pgc-469-1-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<div id=\"panel-469-1-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"1\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n<div id=\"pg-469-0\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\n<p id=\"pgc-469-0-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"1\"><a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-638601140_2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-3175 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-638601140_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"553\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-638601140_2.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-638601140_2-300x199.jpg 300w, https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-638601140_2-768x508.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 553px) 100vw, 553px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pg-469-1\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\n<div id=\"pgc-469-1-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<div id=\"panel-469-1-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"1\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit;\">Our client brought a lawsuit against defendants Michael Bivens and Screen Team, Inc. in the  Fresno Superior Court for breach of contract, fiduciary duties, fraud, interference with business opportunities and contracts, and for declaratory relief. Our client obtained a temporary restraining order and preliminary injunction. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit;\">I was able to defeat all pretrial motions brought by the defendants to change the venue, to increase the bond to $500,000, and was successful with its motions in limine to exclude offsetting evidence that the defendant attempted to introduce into evidence during the trial in the sum of $56,000 due to discovery abuses by the defendant.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>I obtained a $108,000 judgment, a court order confirming that $76,000 in accounts receivables belonged to our client, a permanent injunction ordering the defendants to stop interfering with its business and using its intellectual property rights to compete, and over $4,000 in costs of suit.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pgc-469-1-1\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<div id=\"panel-469-1-1-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-image panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"2\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\u00a0<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n",
    "protected": false
  },
  "excerpt": {
    "rendered": "<p>\u00a0 Our client brought a lawsuit against defendants Michael Bivens and Screen Team, Inc. in the  Fresno Superior Court for breach of contract, fiduciary duties, fraud, interference with business opportunities and contracts, and for declaratory relief. Our client obtained a temporary restraining order and preliminary injunction. I was able to defeat all pretrial motions brought by the defendants to change the venue, to increase the bond to $500,000, and was successful with its motions in limine to exclude offsetting evidence that the defendant attempted to introduce into evidence during the trial in the sum of $56,000 due to discovery&#8230;<\/p>\n",
    "protected": false
  },
